URL reference: https://thenewstack.io/how-to-get-dns-right-a-guide-to-common-failure-modes/
DateReviewed: 2026-01-12
Description: Today's article dives into the mystical world of DNS, and tries to make it a bit more understandable. Kubernetes uses DNS in a lot of places, so having DNS that works properly is important. We start with a short background, and then they dive into why DNS can give us problems. They talk about micro-outages, which are short (minutes to an hour) but hard to diagnose issues. They stem from underlying routing issues, where DNS points to an IP that may not be working. Next up are misconfigs, and these happen all over. Common but tricky issues include CNAME at the apex, missing glue records, bad TTL and lame delegation; they go through each type and how to prevent. They also cover DNS poisoning and Denial of Service (DoS) attacks, which direct users to the wrong server, or just deny the ability to talk to a server at all. Good primer on DNS.
